<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="usual-adj">usual <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'juːʒuəl, 'juːʒəl/    美 /'juːʒuəl, 'juːʒəl/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>平常的：</strong></h4>
<p>反 unusual </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She sat in her usual seat at the back. 
她坐在平常坐的后排的位子上。</p></div>

<h3 id="common-normal-ordinary-usual">辨析 common, normal, ordinary, usual</h3>
<p><strong>common</strong> 侧重表示普遍、常见。
<strong>normal</strong> 侧重指“正常的”、“平常的”。
<strong>ordinary</strong> 侧重表示平常、平凡、无奇特之处。形容人时可与common通用。
<strong>usual</strong> 表示由于长时间没有变化而形成了一种习惯或制度，强调习惯性。</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He arrived later than usual. 
他到得比平时晚。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It is usual for him to sit up late at night. 
他熬夜已成习惯。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="as-usual">as usual</h3>
<p>1.<strong>像平常一样；照例(as always)：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Wang Wei rode in front of me as usual. 
像平时那样，王薇骑车在我的前面。</p><footer>人教① – 3</footer></div></div>